stylometry: You have to first balance the supply of the inventory with the demand for the product.  A company needs to have enough inventory to satisfy the damand, but also not have to much inventory at once.  You have to keep in mind all the things such as fixed costs (ordering cost, holding cost, production cost).  How much to order?  When to order?  Some of the factors that play a role in answering these questions are lead time, cost of holding, and demand. You must find the right amount to where you have enough to cover the demand, but not to much where your holding costs will be higher than necessary.
